narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned about many of the algorithms that can be used to analyze the different set of data and why I should use one algorithm over the other.
current research topics in bioinformatic and main analysis methods
It gives a brief review of different methods in omics. Not many details are involved but it is diverse enough for further explorations.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I thought is was a very good course

The lectures were too fast and covered too many materials. Therefore, it is very hard to follow and digest the knowledge completely. Plus, the homework sometimes is very hard to complete. I think it would be better if Prof. Zhao could put more details in the lecture notes.
this course has wide coverage of bioinformatic researches
Good course to understand the bioinformatics
The strength is the diversity of topics and methods. Each class will give an introduction to a variety of approaches, which may not be that easy to follow for people without experiences.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would definitely reccommend this course to other students.
The course is not very friendly for students without strong background in genetics.
Yes. It is very helpful for students who want to apply statistical methods on biological data. There are many existed tools and it shows when and how to use them.
